headline: A. O. Smith’s (NYSE:AOS) Q1: Beats On Revenue
summary: Water heating and treatment solutions company A.O. Smith (NYSE:AOS) reported Q1 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, but sales fell by 1.5% year on year to $963.9 million. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $3.85 billion at the midpoint came in 0.5% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $0.95 per share was 5.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: A.O. Smith: Q1 Earnings Snapshot
summary: On a per-share basis, the Milwaukee-based company said it had profit of 95 cents. The results topped Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of six analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of 90 cents per share.
